import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
import json

with open('points.json') as f:
    data = pd.json_normalize(json.load(f))

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.hist(data['x'], bins=20, color='blue')
    plt.axvline(data['x'].mean(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label=f"Mean: {data['x'].mean():.2f}")
    plt.axvline(data['x'].median(), color='green', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label=f"Median: {data['x'].median():.2f}")
    plt.xlabel('X-coordinate')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.legend()
    plt.title('What is the distribution of the x-coordinates of the points?')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
plt.show()
```

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    color_counts = data['color'].value_counts()
    colors = color_counts.index
    counts = color_counts.values
    fig, ax = plt.subplots()
    ax.bar(colors, counts, color=colors)
    ax.set_xlabel('Color')
    ax.set_ylabel('Count')
    ax.set_title('What is the distribution of the point colors?')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```
